# Quick Reference

## Scripts

```bash
npm run dev          # nodemon + ts-node (development)
npm run build        # tsc → dist/
npm start            # node dist/bin/www.js
npm run lint:fix     # eslint --fix
npm run format       # prettier --write
npm run db:migrate   # run schema.sql against DB
npm run db:seed      # insert admin user
npm run db:setup     # migrate + seed
npm test             # jest
```

## Response Helpers

```ts
import { success, error } from '../utils/response';

success(res, data);           // 200
success(res, data, 201);      // 201
error(res, 'Not found', 404, 'NOT_FOUND');   return;
error(res, 'Forbidden', 403, 'FORBIDDEN');   return;
```

## DB Helpers

```ts
import { query, withTransaction } from '../config/postgres';

const result = await query<UserRow>('SELECT id, email, role FROM users WHERE id = $1', [id]);
if (result.rowCount && result.rowCount > 0) { ... }

await withTransaction(async (client) => {
  await client.query('SELECT status FROM tickets WHERE id = $1 FOR UPDATE', [id]);
  await client.query('UPDATE tickets SET status = $2 WHERE id = $1', [id, newStatus]);
});
```

## Redis Helpers

```ts
import { setCache, getCache, deleteCache } from '../config/redis';

await setCache('ticket:' + id, ticketData);           // uses config TTL
const cached = await getCache<TicketRow>('ticket:' + id);
await deleteCache('ticket:' + id);
```

Note: `keyPrefix: 'stm:'` is auto-prepended by ioredis — never add it manually.

## Common TypeScript Types

```ts
type UserRole       = 'ADMIN' | 'AGENT';
type TicketStatus   = 'OPEN' | 'IN_PROGRESS' | 'RESOLVED' | 'CLOSED' | 'CANCELLED';
type TicketPriority = 'LOW' | 'MEDIUM' | 'HIGH' | 'URGENT';
```

## Environment Variables (key ones)

```
NODE_ENV=development | test | production
PORT=3000
PG_DATABASE=ttn_stm          (ttn_stm_test in NODE_ENV=test)
JWT_SECRET=changeme           (change in production!)
JWT_EXPIRES_IN=7d
REDIS_KEY_PREFIX=stm:
REDIS_TTL_SECONDS=3600
```

## Error Codes

| Code | Scenario | HTTP |
|---|---|---|
| `VALIDATION_ERROR` | Zod parse failure | 400 |
| `NOT_FOUND` | Resource does not exist | 404 |
| `FORBIDDEN` | Caller lacks permission | 403 |
| `INVALID_STATUS_TRANSITION` | State machine violation | 409 |
| `USER_NOT_FOUND` | `assignedTo` UUID non-existent | 404 |
| `INVALID_COMMENT_REFERENCE` | `commentId` not on parent ticket | 400 |

